name: Planar graph
summary: In graph theory, a planar graph is a graph that can be embedded in the plane, i.e., it can be drawn on the plane in such a way that its edges intersect only at their endpoints.  In other words, it can be drawn in such a way that no edges cross each other.   Such a drawing is called a plane graph, or a planar embedding of the graph.
